  "body": "After chatting with @gaearon - we figured it made more sense to use the merge base for a PR to determine the build size changes instead of the parent commit of the first commit on the branch.\r\n\r\nThis does that, and adds some docs to the header. \r\n\r\n```sh\r\n‚ùØ yarn danger pr https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/12028\r\nyarn run v1.3.2\r\n$ /Users/orta/dev/projects/oss/js/react/node_modules/.bin/danger pr https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/12028\r\nStarting Danger PR on facebook/react#12028\r\n\r\n## Failures\r\n\r\n## Warnings\r\n\r\n## Messages\r\n\r\n## Markdowns\r\nReactDOM: size: :small_red_triangle:+1%, gzip: :small_red_triangle:+2%\r\n-\r\n\r\n  <details>\r\n  <summary>Details of bundled changes.</summary>\r\n\r\n  <p>Comparing: bd6b533c29cc617b4ddfc0a8b623e782c468cd52...8d67e27dbd52eec339543486a8997a2a3a9094ae</p>\r\n\r\n  [snip]\r\n```",
